body:
R: @jbonofre and @kennknowles 
Also PTAL: 
@aviemzur - you had some suggestions for better code reuse.
@amarouni - I've moved some of the "provided" context code into the `SparkContextFactory`.

@amitsela I ran the test submitted as part of PR #901 and it looks good!

I think we can basically close #901, but it might be a good idea to cherry-pick/issue a separate PR for the modified [`SimpleStreamingWordCountTest`](https://github.com/staslev/incubator-beam/blob/BEAM-15-fix-incompatible-StorageLevel/runners/spark/src/test/java/org/apache/beam/runners/spark/translation/streaming/SimpleStreamingWordCountTest.java), which tests multiple batches instead of just one.

What do you think?

@aviemzur I generally agree, but since the DStream/RDD API are separate APIs (reusable to some extent, with further limitations once checkpointing is enabled) you'll end up asking this wrapper (for example, in streaming pipelines that have "batch/bounded" branches)  if it's a DStream or an RDD in order to address the appropriate `TransformTranslator` and pcollections map.
The current status duplicates code, which I'm not thrilled about, but keeps a good separation between streaming and batch translations.

Would your suggestion be relevant as part of future work following this PR, or will it require another/different refactor of the translation mechanism ?

@kennknowles the integration tests are now enabled and results can be seen in Jenkins (96 failures).

Any thought on how to handle the following (from CountingInputTest etc.) ?

GroupByKey cannot be applied to non-bounded PCollection in the GlobalWindow without a trigger. Use a Window.into or Window.triggering transform prior to GroupByKey.

@amitsela I see that there already exists code that decides which translator to use , in any case this can be solved by having the wrappers delegate the call to org/apache/beam/runners/spark/translation/TransformTranslator.translate()
or
org/apache/beam/runners/spark/translation/streaming/StreamingTransformTranslator.translate()
